properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 27 at 3:16AM PST until January 28 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Spokane WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected above 3000 feet. Total snow accumulations
of 4 to 12 inches, with up to 18 inches along the crest.

* WHERE...Stevens Pass, Blewett Pass, Loup Loup Pass, and Holden
Village.

* WHEN...From 4 PM this afternoon to 10 AM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The heaviest snow will fall through the
evening hours.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 10 AM PST TUESDAY ABOVE 3000 FEET
